---
title: Chicken Sausage Pasta e Fagioli Soup with Garlicky Breadsticks & Parsley
description: This soul-warming vegan soup is the culinary equivalent of a cozy blanket. It’s chock full of goodness, with earthy cannellini and kidney beans, tender onion and celery, and springy couscous in a savory tomato and mushroom broth. Throw in lots of fresh parsley, serve with a side of crisp garlic breadsticks, and you’ve got an ideal vegan dinner or lunch idea! Get ready to wrap yourself in this meal that’s as satisfying and comforting as it is delicious.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/665df043bb68d6ba93ee199b-91a11370.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/675a1a45daedc2bd1295b018-en-US.pdf
time required: 35m
nutrition:
  calories: 930 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 106 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 2550 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-sausage-pasta-e-fagioli-soup-675a1a45daedc2bd1295b018
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces). Halve @celery{2.5%ounce} lengthwise; dice into 1/4-inch pieces. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%can} and @kidney beans{1%can}. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}. Reserve #pot{}.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onion, celery, @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{} to taste. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and lightly browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> If onion browns too quickly, add a splash of water and lower heat.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce can}, half the cannellini beans, half the kidney beans, 2 cups water, and a big pinch of salt and pepper (use all the cannellini and kidney beans and 4 cups water for 4 servings).

Increase heat to medium high and bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beans and couscous are tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Use pot used for sausage here. Once beans and couscous are tender, stir sausage into soup.

Meanwhile, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise; slice each half lengthwise into thirds.

In a #large bowl{}, toss baguette pieces with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, remaining garlic powder, and salt and pepper to taste until evenly coated. Arrange seasoned baguette pieces on a #baking sheet{} and bake on top rack until lightly toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove baking sheet from oven; carefully flip breadsticks and return to top rack until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide soup between #bowls{}; garnish with parsley. Serve with breadsticks on the side.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.